READ ME

$> mvn install

Find .jar file in "target" directory.

In order to run service.

java -jar <(Path) + JAR file name> server <name of config file>

My specific example
$> java -jar target/my-project-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT.jar server hello-world.yml


Test the service by pointing browser to

http://localhost:8080/hello-world
or 
http://localhost:8080/hello-world?name=Successful+Dropwizard+User

Admin port at

http://localhost:8081/

Thread check at
http://localhost:8081/threads